#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
README
======
Filename:
    ghost_topper_safe.py

Purpose:
    Display a terminal-only intro topper safely, then return control to the
    main Python program without contaminating later output or terminal state.

What is new in this version:
    - 20 distinct built-in visual designs
    - Random or explicit design selection
    - Strong terminal safety / restoration
    - Alternate-screen isolation
    - Graceful fail-open behavior
    - Reusable helper for all future scripts

Safety model:
    - Runs only on interactive TTY terminals
    - Skips itself automatically in unsafe environments
    - Uses alternate screen buffer so normal terminal content is restored
    - Hides cursor temporarily and always restores it
    - Wraps terminal state changes in try/finally
    - Does not modify globals used by the rest of your program
    - Does not monkeypatch stdout/stderr
    - Does not spawn background output that can collide with later prints

Recommended use:
    Put this near the top of your script file, then call:
        run_ghost_topper_safe(total_seconds=10, design="random")

Environment assumptions:
    - Linux / POSIX terminal
    - ANSI-capable terminal preferred
    - Safe fallback: if not supported, topper is skipped cleanly

Behavior:
    - Approx. 10 second runtime by default
    - Countdown
    - One of 20 visual designs
    - Restores terminal and returns
"""

